      • isApplicable

        public boolean isApplicable(BasicObligation obl)
        Description copied from interface: Processor
        this is a short test whether this processor can in general handle this kind of basic obligation. This information will be used for two things. First, if the processor says that it is not applicable, it will not be tried with process. (Hence, all input passed to process will be checked with isApplicable) Second, in an interactive mode, this method can be used to determine which processors may be applied to the currently selected obligation.

        Parameters:
        inRule - some rule
        lhsPrefix - the prefix used for the (bound) variables on the left and fresh variables
        rhsPrefix - the prefix used for the new variables
        factory - some formula factory
        Returns:
        a pair of formulae, the first encoding the variable updates, the second the conditions

      • moveFsIntoArgsAndNormalize

        public static java.util.Set<IGeneralizedRule> moveFsIntoArgsAndNormalize(java.util.Set<IGeneralizedRule> rules)
        Chooses a map m from existing function symbols to an integer. Then turns rules like f(x1, ..., xn) -> g(t1, ..., tm) | c into a new rule f(pc, x1, ..., xn, y1 ..., yk) -> g(map(r), t1, ..., tm, z1, ..., zl) | pc = map(f) && c such that n + k = argNum and m + l = argNum holds. We will then later just ignore the enclosing symbols.
        Parameters:
        rules - some rules
        Returns:
        the modified rules

      • moveFsIntoArgs

        Parameters:
        rule - Some rule f(x1, ..., xn) -> g(t1, ..., tm) | c
        argNum - number of arguments every term should have after we are done (plus one for the pc). Should be at least the max of the arity of all occurring defined symbols
        pcMap - map from function symbols to integer
        Returns:
